	(text "V_bus = 170V DC, I_motor = 8A, f_sw = 8kHz (T=125µs)\nMOSFET: STP20NM60FP (Q_g = 30nC)\nDriver: IR2136 (V_CC = 15V, V_UVLO = 8.2V, Q_ls = 20nC max)\nDiode: UF4007 (V_R = 1000V, V_f = 1.1V @ 0.5A, t_rr = 75ns, Q_rr ≈ 20nC)\nCapacitor: 150nF 100V X7R (ceramic) + 10µF 100V (electrolytic) per phase\nResistor: 4.7Ω 0.5W 1206 (R_boot)\nProtection: SMAJ18CA TVS across C_boot (clamps >18V spikes)\nQ_total = (Q_g + Q_ls + Q_rr) × Margin = (30 + 20 + 20) × 1.5 = 105 nC\nMin C_boot = Q_total / ΔV_max = 105nC / 1.5V = 70 nF → USE 150nF (DC bias derating)\nActual ΔV = Q_total / C_boot = 105nC / 150nF = 0.7V (14V → 13.3V, above UVLO)\nV_boot_max = V_CC_max - VS_min = (15V×1.1) - (-0.35×170V) = 16.5V - (-59.5V) = 76V\nRequired rating = 76V × 1.25 margin = 95V → **USE 100V MINIMUM**\n25V CAPS WILL FAIL WHEN PHASE SWINGS NEGATIVE!\nRecharge ΔV = V_CC - V_f - V_boot_low = 15V - 1.1V - 13.3V = 0.6V\nWith 4.7Ω: I_peak = 0.6V / (4.7Ω + 0.8Ω_diode) = 109mA (safe)\nRecharge time: t_charge = 3 × R_total × C = 3 × 5.5Ω × 150nF = 2.48µs\nT_off_min = t_charge + t_dead + margin = 2.48µs + 2.0µs + 0.5µs = 4.98µs\nDuty_max = 120µs / 125µs = 96.0%\nDeadtime_min = 2.0µs (shoot-through protection)\nR_boot: P_peak = I_peak² × R = (0.109A)² × 4.7Ω = 56mW → USE 0.5W\nUF4007: P_diode = V_f × I_avg ≈ 1.1V × 10mA = 11mW (negligible)\n[✓] V_boot_min = 13.3V > V_UVLO (8.2V) + margin (2V) = 10.2V\n[✓] Recharge (2.48µs) fits in T_off (5.0µs)\n[✓] Duty limit (96%) achievable with control algorithm\n[✓] 100V rating > worst-case 76V\n[✓] Peak current 109mA < UF4007 rating (1A continuous)"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
